# Chapter 2: Getting Data in and out of R
## 2.1 Reading and Writing Data
The main functions for getting data into R
* `read.table` and `read.csv` for reading in tabular data
* `readLines` for reading lines of a text file
* `source` for reading in R code files (opposite of `dump`)
* `dget` for readingin R code files (opposite of `dput`)
* `load` for reading in save workspaces
* `unserialize` for reading single R objects in binary form

The main functions for writing data from R
* `write.table` for writing tabular data to text files
* `writeLines` for writing character data line-by-line to a file or
connection
* `dump` for dumping textual representation of multiple R objects
* `dput` for outputting a textual representation of an R object
* `save` for saving an arbitrary number of R objects in a binary
format
* `serialize` for converting an R object into a binary format for
  outputting to a connection


